Document: GPUParticlesCollision3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_gpuparticlescollision3d.rst  
Summary: Controls which particle rendering layers are affected by collision shapes.  

Property: cull_mask (int) = 4294967295  
Sets the particle rendering layers (VisualInstance3D.layers) that will be affected by the collision shape. By default, all particles with ParticleProcessMaterial.collision_mode set to ParticleProcessMaterial.COLLISION_RIGID or ParticleProcessMaterial.COLLISION_HIDE_ON_CONTACT are affected. After configuring particle nodes, specific layers can be unchecked to exclude certain particles from collision interactions. For example, this can prevent a spell effect collider from affecting unrelated weather particles at the same position.  

Method: set_cull_mask(value: int) → void  
Method: get_cull_mask() → int  

Note: Particle collision can also be disabled on a per-process material basis by setting ParticleProcessMaterial.collision_mode on the GPUParticles3D node.